    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Algolia is focused on search, that means that people should search for a result, and then refine, if people are searching for something they don't find on the first few pages, they will usually refine differently. \r\n\r\nSince changing a page in InstantSearch doesn't require a full page request, changing a page here is almost negligible qua user impact.\r\n\r\nIf you want a bit more than 20 hits per page, you can change the [hitsPerPage](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/api-parameters/hitsPerPage/) parameter, and if that still isn't enough, you can take a look at [paginationLimitedTo](https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/searching/pagination/#overriding-the-default-limits).\r\n\r\nIf you want to get all the results of an index for some specific use case, you can use [browse](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-client/php/advanced/#backup--export-an-index)",
    "created_at": "2017-07-20T13:10:07Z",
